.\" ###### Setup ############################################################
.Dd May 9, 2026
.Dt gs\-oilify 1
.Os gs\-oilify
.\" ###### Name #############################################################
.Sh NAME
.Nm gs\-oilify
.Nd applies the GIMP GEGL "Oilify" filter on an image
.\" ###### Synopsis #########################################################
.\" Manpage syntax help:
.\" https://forums.freebsd.org/threads/howto-create-a-manpage-from-scratch.13200/
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm gs\-oilify Ar input\_filename Ar output\_filename
.br
.Op Fl S Ar masksize | Fl Fl mask\-size Ar masksize
.br
.Op Fl I Ar on|off | Fl Fl intensity\-mode Ar on|off
.br
.Op Fl q | Fl Fl quiet
.Op Fl w | Fl Fl verbose
.Nm gs\-oilify
.Op Fl h | Fl Fl help
.Nm gs\-oilify
.Op Fl v | Fl Fl version
.\" ###### Description ######################################################
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm gs\-oilify
runs GIMP to load an image, and applies the GIMP GEGL "Oilify" filter
(details:
.Lk https://gegl.org/operations/gegl\-oilify.html "GEGL Oilify" )
and stores the result into an output file.
.Pp
.\" ###### Arguments ########################################################
.Sh ARGUMENTS
The following options are available:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Ar input\_filename
The input image. Any format supported by GIMP can be used. The format will be detected automatically.
.It Ar output\_filename
The name for the output image to be written. Any format supported by GIMP can be used. The format will be detected by the provided file name extension (e.g. .jpeg, .png, .webp, .pdf, ...). An existing output file will be overwritten.
.It Fl S Ar masksize | Fl Fl mask\-size Ar masksize
Specifies the mask size. Range: 2\-200. Default: 8.
.It Fl I Ar on|off | Fl Fl intensity\-mode Ar on|off
Turns intensity mode on or off. Default: on.
.It Fl q | Fl Fl quiet
Quiet mode: suppress GIMP console output. This is the default.
.It Fl w | Fl Fl verbose
Verbose mode: print GIMP console output and processing details.
.It Fl h | Fl Fl help
Prints the program's command\-line parameters and exits.
.It Fl v | Fl Fl version
Prints the program version and exits.
.El
.\" ###### Exit status ######################################################
.Sh EXIT STATUS
The
.Nm
tool exits with 0 on success, and >0 in case of an error.
.\" ###### Examples #########################################################
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It gs\-oilify Bergen.jpeg Bergen\-Oilify.png \-S 12 \-I off
.It gs\-oilify Bergen.jpeg Bergen\-Oilify.webp \-\-mask\-size 10 \-\-verbose
.It gs\-oilify \-\-help
.It gs\-oilify \-h
.It gs\-oilify \-\-version
.It gs\-oilify \-v
.El
